transfers.body:
Application data (accounts, profiles, content, logs) is stored and processed exclusively in the European Union (Supabase eu-west-3 Paris, Vercel CDG, Sentry sentry.de.io). No application transfer takes place to the United States or other third countries.

Since the parent companies of these providers (Vercel Inc., Supabase Inc., Resend Inc., Functional Software Inc.) are based in the United States, administrative transfers (billing, support) may occur. They are governed by:
• the European Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs), 2021 version (decision 2021/914);
• the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework where the provider is certified;
• additional technical measures: TLS 1.3, AES-256 encryption at rest, principle of least privilege.

If you use Google, GitHub or Discord OAuth sign-in, the OAuth provider applies its own transfer policy.
